---
description: Force agent to read memory-bank before any significant action
alwaysApply: true
---

## What This Rule Does

Before generating code, writing specs, running any skill, or answering any
non-trivial question, the agent reads the memory-bank to understand what
project it is in, what patterns are established, and what is currently being
worked on. This prevents the agent from making assumptions that contradict
the project's conventions and stops it from duplicating in-flight work.

**As of this phase, this also means checking `repo-discovery` freshness.**
Memory-bank's Tier 1 files are narrative and can lag the live codebase between
`/context-sync` runs; `.cursor/cache/repo-map.json` (owned by `/repo-discovery`,
see `.cursor/docs/skill-graph.md`) is the machine-checkable layer underneath
it. Any skill about to generate or audit code checks `repo-map.json`'s own
freshness (Step 0 of `/repo-discovery`) rather than trusting memory-bank's
prose alone — this is what keeps the workspace reliable on large, fast-moving
repos.

**Memory-bank is two-tiered** — see `memory-bank/README.md` for the full
breakdown. Tier 1 (`techContext.md`, `systemPatterns.md`, `projectbrief.md`,
`productContext.md`, `progress.md`, `activeContext.md`, `techDebt.md`,
`WORKING_ON.md`) is a live snapshot regenerated by `/context-sync` and kept
current by this rule. Tier 2 (`architecture.md`, `codingStandards.md`,
`businessRules.md`, `technologyStack.md`, `databaseConventions.md`,
`apiConventions.md`, `frontendConventions.md`, `backendConventions.md`,
`securityStandards.md`, `performanceGuidelines.md`, `testingStandards.md`,
`deploymentNotes.md`, `decisionLog.md`, `commonMistakes.md`, `glossary.md`)
is human-authored standards content — never auto-regenerated, only read.
Step 1 below covers Tier 1, which changes every session. Tier 2 is read
on-demand by the specific skill/rule it applies to (each skill now lists
which Tier 2 files it reads under "Memory references" in its Overview).

**MCP tools (cross-cutting):** if the `context7` MCP server is connected, any
`*-gen` skill generating code against a specific library version should
resolve that version from `technologyStack.md`/`techContext.md` and pull its
actual current docs via Context7 before generating — prevents the class of
bug `commonMistakes.md` exists to catch after the fact (training-data-era API
usage against a newer pinned library version). See `.cursor/docs/mcp-ecosystem.md`.

